  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em>You sprinkle a tiny bit of holy water or powdered silver and cold iron on an ally, offering a prayer and warding them from harm from certain magical creatures.</em></p><p><strong>Buff</strong></p><p>The target is protected against certain types of creatures: &amp;reference[aberration], &amp;reference[celestial], &amp;reference[elemental], &amp;reference[fey], &amp;reference[fiend], and &amp;reference[undead].</p><ul><li><p>Creatures of those types have disadvantage on attack rolls against the target.</p></li><li><p>The target can't be &amp;reference[charmed], &amp;reference[frightened], or possessed by those types of creatures. If the target is already charmed, frightened, or possessed by such a creature, the target has advantage on any new saving throw against the relevant effect.</p></li></ul>",
      "chat": "<p><strong>Buff</strong></p><p>The target is protected against certain types of creatures: &amp;reference[aberration], &amp;reference[celestial], &amp;reference[elemental], &amp;reference[fey], &amp;reference[fiend], and &amp;reference[undead].</p><ul><li><p>Creatures of those types have disadvantage on attack rolls against the target.</p></li><li><p>The target can't be &amp;reference[charmed], &amp;reference[frightened], or possessed by those types of creatures. If the target is already charmed, frightened, or possessed by such a creature, the target has advantage on any new saving throw against the relevant effect.</p></li></ul>"
    },
